<inglise> Council Regulation (EC, ECSC, Euratom) No 628/2000 of 20 March 2000 amending Regulation (EC, Euratom, ECSC) No 259/68 laying down the Staff Regulations of Officials of the European Communities and the Conditions of Employment of Other Servants of the Communities </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;, EST&Uuml;, EURATOM) nr 628/2000, millega muudetakse m&auml;&auml;rust (E&Uuml;, Euratom, EST&Uuml;) nr 259/68, millega kehtestatakse Euroopa &uuml;henduste ametnike personalieeskirjad ja &uuml;henduste muude teenistujate teenistustingimused 20. m&auml;rts 2000 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, and in particular Article 283 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 283, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission presented after consulting the Staff Regulations Committee(1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse ettepanekut, mille komisjon esitas p&auml;rast n&otilde;upidamist personalieeskirjade komiteega, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament(2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Court of Justice(3), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Kohtu arvamust, (3) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Court of Auditors(4), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Kontrollikoja arvamust (4) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas: </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) With a view to equal treatment, conference interpreters engaged on behalf of the Community institutions and bodies should be subject to the same legal arrangements. </inglise>
<eesti> 1) v&otilde;rdset kohtlemist silmas pidades tuleks &uuml;henduse institutsioonide ja organite teenistuses olevate konverentsit&otilde;lkide suhtes kohaldada samu &otilde;igusnorme; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) All conference interpreters should consequently be engaged as auxiliary staff covered by Title III of the Conditions of Employment of Other Servants of the European Communities, </inglise>
<eesti> 2) k&otilde;ik konverentsit&otilde;lgid tuleks seet&otilde;ttu t&ouml;&ouml;le v&otilde;tta Euroopa &uuml;henduste muude teenistujate teenistustingimuste III jaotisega h&otilde;lmatud abiteenistujatena, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> The following paragraph shall be added to Article 78 of the Conditions of Employment of Other Servants of the European Communities: " The same conditions of recruitment and remuneration applied to conference interpreters engaged by the European Parliament shall apply to auxiliary staff engaged by the Commission as conference interpreters on behalf of the Community institutions and bodies." </inglise>
<eesti> Euroopa &uuml;henduste muude teenistujate teenistustingimuste artiklile 78 lisatakse j&auml;rgmine l&otilde;ik: "Abiteenistujate suhtes, kelle komisjon v&otilde;tab &uuml;henduse institutsioonide ja organite nimel t&ouml;&ouml;le konverentsit&otilde;lkidena, kohaldatakse samu t&ouml;&ouml;lev&otilde;tu- ja tasustamistingimusi kui Euroopa Parlamendi poolt t&ouml;&ouml;lev&otilde;etud konverentsit&otilde;lkide suhtes." </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the day following that of its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub j&auml;rgmisel p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
